{"title_page": "Kartarpur, India", "text_new": "{{For|town KARTARPUR, DISTT-JALANDHAR (PUNJAB) INDIA\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| Name OF CITY            = '''KARTARPUR.\nWard in City              =     15\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = pa\n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = TOWN\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India (Punjab)India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Punjab,India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|31.44|N|75.5|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of INDIA [State]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Jalandhar district|Jalandhar]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = Sri Guru Arjan Dev Ji 5TH Guru\n| named_for               = \n| government_type          = [[Municipal Council] \n| | governing_body          = [[Municipal Council]]\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          =  \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 228\n| population_total        = 25662\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 144801\n| area_code_type          = Telephone code\n| area_code               = 0181-\n| registration_plate      = PB 08\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Kartarpur''' is a town near the city of [[Jalandhar]] and is located in the [[Doaba]] region of the state. It was founded by the fifth Guru of Sikhs, [[Sri Guru Arjan Dev Ji]].\n\n==Geography==\nKartarpur is located at {{Coord|31.44|N|75.5|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/23/Kartarpur.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Kartarpur]</ref> It has an average elevation of 228&nbsp;metres (748&nbsp;feet).\nIt is situated at a distance of 15 & nbsp;km from Jalandhar towards Amritsar on G.T. Road (National Highway 1).\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Kartarpur had a population of 25,662. Males constitute 54% of the population and females 46%. Kartarpur has an average literacy rate of 69%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 72%, and female literacy is 66%. In Kartarpur, 12% of the population is under 6 years of age. Kartarpur has 15 municipal wards.\n\n==Jang e Azadi Kartarpur Museum==\n{{Main|Jang-e-Azadi Memorial}}\n\nJang-e-Azadi Memorial is a memorial and museum being built in Kartarpur town of Punjab, India, in memory of contribution and sacrifices made by the Punjabi community in Indian independence movement.\n\n==Religion==\n\n[[Gurudwara]]s include:\n\n1. Gurudwara Shri Thamji Sahib Near Qila kothi kartarpur\n2. Gurudwara Mata Gujri Ji Gali Mata Gujri Kartarpur\n3. Gurudwara Shri Gangsar Sahib Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n4. Gurdwara Baba Barhbhag singh Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n5. First Guru Granth Sahib(Adi Granth) is placed at Qila Kothi (Kartarpur Fort).\n6. Gurdwara Bibi Nanki Ji G.T.Road Kartarpur\n*Gurudwara Shri Mai Bhago Ji\n*Gurudwara Tahli Sahib\n*Gurdwara pind khusropur, khusropur \nLocated in the middle of village khusropur.\nAlso a new gurdwara is taking place near the previous gurdwara of khusropur.\n*Ramgarhia gurdwara, Khusropur \nLocated on the road connecting village khusropur with village basrampur.\n*Gurdwara basrampur, Basrampur.\n[[TEMPLES]] include:\n1. Nathan Di Bagichi (Nath welfare society, Jande sarai road )This temple is belongs to Nath Welfair socity Regd. who worship Bhagwan Mahadev Shiv\n2. Bute Shah Di Bagichi Jande sarai Road Kartarpur\n3. Ganu Di Bagichi Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n4. Barahmcharian Bagichi Vishvkarma Market Kartarpur\n5. Jassa Mall da Talab Bagichi Bholath Road Kartarpur\n6. Prachin Mata Chintpurni Mandir Dyalpur Gate Kartarpur\n7. New Mata Chintpurni Mandir Jande sarai Road Kartarpur\n8. Parachin Shiv mandir pandhian Bazar kartarpur\n9. Prachin Shiv Mandir Sekhrian Mohalla Kartarpur\n10. Jyoti Moti Mandir Gangsar Bazar Kartarpur\n11. Chidian Mandir Khalipha Gate kartarpur\n12. Kesaran Mandir Mohalla Kale wala Kartarpur\n13. Rama Krishana Mandir Mohalla Imli Wala Kartarpur\n14  Sitla Mandir Gangsar Bazar Kartarpur\n15. Sitla/Gaushala Mandir Bania Bazar Kartarpur\n16. Hanuman Mandir Bania Bazar Kartarpur\n17. Prachin shiv Mandir Katni Gate Kartarpur\n18. Prachin shiv Mandir Near Gurdwara Gangsar sahib Kartarpur\n19. Loharan Mandir mohalla Kartarpur\n20. Banian Mandir mohalla Banian Kartarpur\n21. Shri Guru Ravidass Mandir Arya Nagar Kartarpur\n22. Shri Guru Ravidass Mandir Furniture Bazar Kartarpur\n23. Shri Guru Ravidass Mandir Gali Araian Dyalpur Gate Kartarpur\n24  Dera/Bagichi baba Gurmukh dass Chandan nagar Kartarpur\n24. Bhagwan balmik Mandir Rishi Nagar Kartarpur\n25. Bhagwan balmik Mandir Mandi Mohalla Kartarpur\n26. Bagichi Baba Bhagtu Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n27. Bagwan Parshuram Mandir katni Gate Kartarpur\n28. Sethan Mandir Muhalla bhai Bhara Kartarpur\n29. Vigan da Mandir Delhi Gate Kartarpur\n30. Mata Veshno Mandir Gangsar Bazar Kartarpur\n30. Mandir Surian Khalifa Gate Kartarpur\n31. Sonian Mandir Kalifa Gate Kartarpur\n32 Guru Ravidass Dharmshala Arya Nagar Kartarpur\n33. Guru Ravidass Mandir Dr. ambedkar Nagar Kartarpur\n*Dera 108 Sant Baba Onkar Nath Ji Maharaj Village [[Kala Bahian]] Dera Baba Onkar Nath Ji is located in village Kala Bahian, Lakhs of Sangat visit Dera every year. There is Holy Sarowar inside Dera, holy water of Sarowar cures Many Problems of Persons. 108 Baba Onkar Nath ji belongs to Nath Sampradaye who worship Bhagwan Shiv, Baba Balak Nath Ji also belongs to Nath  Sampradaye.\n\n[[Mosque]] include :\n\n1. Badi masjid or madeena masjid New vishawkarma market\n2. Choti masjid Old Katni Gate Kartarpur\n\n==Locality==\n1. Arya Nagar Kartarpur,2.Chandan Nagar Kartarpur 3. Adarsh Nagar Colony 4. Shivpuri Colony 5.Gandhi Nagar Colony 6.Katni Gate Colony 7.Sethan Mohalla 8.Bohar Wala mohalla 9. Charkhri Mohalla 10.Dyalpur Gate 11.Rishi Nagar 13. vishvkarma Market 14. Tulsi Nagar 15 Basant Vihar Colony 16.Ambedkar Nagar 17.ShekhWan Colony 18.Pritam Nagar 19.Mohalla Mandi Wala 20. Baljot Nagar 21. Mohalla Bauli Wala 22 Gainda mohalla 23.Barandari Mohalla 24.Inli Wali Gali 25.Hospital Street 26.mohalla Kaulsar 27.Surian mohalla 28. Chodian mohalla 29. muhalla Akaalgarh 30. Sakian Street 31.Bhallian Street 32.Mohalla Banian 33.Khatikam Mohalla 34.Russi Watan Mohalla 35 Delhi Gate 36. Purani Kotwali 37 jand Wali Gali 38.Loharan Wali Gali 39.Sonian Street 40.Kalifa Gate 41.Bhanjhrian Street 42. Pakka Bag.43. Galli Molvi Ajiz 44. Phullan Street 45. Kale Wala Mohalla 46. Dafter Wali Gali 47. Gali matt Wali 48. Malhana Street 49.Chodrian Street 50.Mata Gujri Street 51.Tikrian mohalla 52. Suderian Street 53. Ramgaria Street 55. Mohalla BhaiBhara 56.Kesran Street 57.Bhardwaj Street 58.Sekhrian Street 59.Kucha Gulab Singh 60.Nivi Gali 61\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=32367 Jalandhar district]\n{{Jalandhar district}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Jalandhar district]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|town KARTARPUR, DISTT-JALANDHAR (PUNJAB) INDIA\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| Name OF CITY            = '''KARTARPUR.\nWard in City              =     15\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = pa\n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = TOWN\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India (Punjab)India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Punjab,India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|31.44|N|75.5|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of INDIA [State]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Jalandhar district|Jalandhar]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = Sri Guru Arjan Dev Ji 5TH Guru\n| named_for               = \n| government_type          = [[Municipal Council] \n| | governing_body          = [[Municipal Council]]\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          =  \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 228\n| population_total        = 25662\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 144801\n| area_code_type          = Telephone code\n| area_code               = 0181-\n| registration_plate      = PB 08\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Kartarpur''' is a town near the city of [[Jalandhar]] and is located in the [[Doaba]] region of the state. It was founded by the fifth Guru of Sikhs, [[Sri Guru Arjan Dev Ji]].\n\n==Geography==\nKartarpur is located at {{Coord|31.44|N|75.5|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/23/Kartarpur.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Kartarpur]</ref> It has an average elevation of 228&nbsp;metres (748&nbsp;feet).\nIt is situated at a distance of 15 & nbsp;km from Jalandhar towards Amritsar on G.T. Road (National Highway 1).\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2001}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Kartarpur had a population of 25,152. Males constitute 54% of the population and females 46%. Kartarpur has an average literacy rate of 69%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 72%, and female literacy is 66%. In Kartarpur, 12% of the population is under 6 years of age. Kartarpur has 15 municipal wards.\n\n==Jang e Azadi Kartarpur Museum==\n{{Main|Jang-e-Azadi Memorial}}\n\nJang-e-Azadi Memorial is a memorial and museum being built in Kartarpur town of Punjab, India, in memory of contribution and sacrifices made by the Punjabi community in Indian independence movement.\n\n==Religion==\n\n[[Gurudwara]]s include:\n\n1. Gurudwara Shri Thamji Sahib Near Qila kothi kartarpur\n2. Gurudwara Mata Gujri Ji Gali Mata Gujri Kartarpur\n3. Gurudwara Shri Gangsar Sahib Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n4. Gurdwara Baba Barhbhag singh Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n5. First Guru Granth Sahib(Adi Granth) is placed at Qila Kothi (Kartarpur Fort).\n6. Gurdwara Bibi Nanki Ji G.T.Road Kartarpur\n*Gurudwara Shri Mai Bhago Ji\n*Gurudwara Tahli Sahib\n*Gurdwara pind khusropur, khusropur \nLocated in the middle of village khusropur.\nAlso a new gurdwara is taking place near the previous gurdwara of khusropur.\n*Ramgarhia gurdwara, Khusropur \nLocated on the road connecting village khusropur with village basrampur.\n*Gurdwara basrampur, Basrampur.\n[[TEMPLES]] include:\n1. Nathan Di Bagichi (Nath welfare society, Jande sarai road )This temple is belongs to Nath Welfair socity Regd. who worship Bhagwan Mahadev Shiv\n2. Bute Shah Di Bagichi Jande sarai Road Kartarpur\n3. Ganu Di Bagichi Kishangarh Road Kartarpur\n4. Barahmcharian Bagichi Vishvkarma Market Kartarpur\n5. Jassa Mall da Talab Bagichi Bholath Road Kartarpur\n6. Prachin Mata Chintpurni Mandir Dyalpur Gate Kartarpur\n7. New Mata Chintpurni Mandir Jande sarai Road Kartarpur\n8. Parachin Shiv mandir pandhian Bazar kartarpur\n9. Prachin Shiv Mandir Sekhrian Mohalla Kartarpur\n10. Jyoti Moti Mandir Gangsar Bazar Kartarpur\n11. Chidian Mandir Khalipha Gate kartarpur\n12. Kesaran Mandir Mohalla Kale wala Kartarpur\n13. Rama Krishana Mandir Mohalla Imli Wala Kartarpur\n14  Sitla Mandir Gangsar Bazar Kartarpur\n15. Sitla/Gaushala Mandir Bania Bazar Kartarpur\n16. Hanuman Mandir Bania Bazar Kartarpur\n17. Prachin shiv Mandir Katni Gate Kartarpur\n18. Prachin shiv Mandir Near Gurdwara Gangsar sahib Kartarpur\n19. Loharan Mandir mohalla Kartarpur\n20. Banian Mandir m